  "text": "API server audit logging in kubernetes/kubernetes is implemented through a comprehensive system spanning multiple packages in staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/. The system follows a modular architecture with clear separation of concerns:\n\n## Core Audit Infrastructure\n\nThe audit event creation from requests starts with the audit context initialization in pkg/endpoints/filters/audit_init.go via WithAuditInit(), which creates an AuditContext and generates or captures an Audit-ID. The main audit filter in pkg/endpoints/filters/audit.go (WithAudit) evaluates the audit policy and creates audit events at multiple stages (RequestReceived, ResponseStarted, ResponseComplete, Panic).\n\nAudit event creation involves:\n- pkg/audit/context.go: AuditContext holds the Event and RequestAuditConfig for the current request\n- pkg/audit/request.go: Core functions LogRequestMetadata(), LogRequestObject(), LogResponseObject(), and LogImpersonatedUser() populate audit event fields from requests and responses\n- pkg/audit/format.go: EventString() formats events in legacy text format\n\n## Audit Policy Evaluation\n\nPolicy evaluation is handled through the PolicyRuleEvaluator interface in pkg/audit/evaluator.go. The concrete implementation:\n- pkg/audit/policy/checker.go: NewPolicyRuleEvaluator() and EvaluatePolicyRule() match request attributes against policy rules to determine audit level and omit stages\n- pkg/audit/policy/reader.go: LoadPolicyFromFile() loads and validates the audit policy from a YAML file\n- pkg/audit/policy/util.go: Utility functions for policy matching\n\n## Audit Backend Dispatch\n\nThe audit backend dispatch system supports multiple backends simultaneously through:\n- pkg/audit/types.go: Defines the Sink and Backend interfaces that all backends must implement\n- pkg/audit/union.go: Union() function combines multiple backends into a single Backend that dispatches events to all backends\n- pkg/server/options/audit.go: AuditOptions and ApplyTo() method orchestrate backend creation and composition\n\n## Audit Backends\n\nThree main backend types handle event persistence and dispatch:\n\n1. **Log File Backend** (pkg/audit/plugin/pkg/audit/log/backend.go):\n   - NewBackend() creates a file-based audit logger\n   - Supports both legacy (1-line text) and JSON formats\n   - Logs events to files with rotation support via lumberjack\n\n2. **Webhook Backend** (pkg/audit/plugin/pkg/audit/webhook/webhook.go):\n   - NewBackend() creates an HTTP webhook client\n   - Sends batches of audit events to external services\n   - Implements retry logic with exponential backoff\n   - Uses kubeconfig format for endpoint configuration\n\n3. **Buffered Backend** (pkg/audit/plugin/pkg/audit/buffered/buffered.go):\n   - NewBackend() wraps delegate backends with buffering\n   - Batches events before forwarding to delegate\n   - Supports throttling and async delegation\n   - Configurable batch size and wait time\n\n## Audit Truncation for Large Bodies\n\nThe truncate backend (pkg/audit/plugin/pkg/audit/truncate/truncate.go) handles oversized events:\n- NewBackend() wraps delegate backends to enforce size limits\n- Monitors individual event size (MaxEventSize) and batch size (MaxBatchSize)\n- Removes RequestObject and ResponseObject from events that exceed MaxEventSize\n- Marks truncated events with audit.k8s.io/truncated=true annotation\n- Splits batches that exceed MaxBatchSize across multiple delegate calls\n\n## Request/Response Logging Integration\n\nRequest and response bodies are logged at handler level:\n- pkg/endpoints/handlers/create.go: LogRequestObject() during create operations\n- pkg/endpoints/handlers/update.go: LogRequestObject() during update operations\n- pkg/endpoints/handlers/delete.go: LogRequestObject() during delete operations\n- Response objects are logged when the response is written\n\n## Server Configuration and Lifecycle\n\nThe complete audit system is integrated into the API server:\n- pkg/server/config.go: Server configuration includes AuditBackend and AuditPolicyRuleEvaluator\n- pkg/server/genericapiserver.go: GenericAPIServer manages backend lifecycle (Run/Shutdown)\n- pkg/server/options/audit.go: Command-line flag handling and backend initialization\n\nThe backend initialization chain in ApplyTo() creates policy evaluators, instantiates log and webhook backends, wraps them with buffering/truncation as configured, and combines them via Union().\n\n## Admission and Context Integration\n\n- pkg/admission/audit.go: WithAudit() wraps admission handlers to log annotations into the audit event\n- pkg/endpoints/filters/request_deadline.go: WithRequestDeadline() handles audit for timeout-related errors\n\nThe audit system uses Go context to thread the AuditContext through the entire request pipeline, allowing any handler to access the current audit event via audit.AuditContextFrom() and audit.AuditEventFrom()."
